        "body": "## Summary\n- restore Amp usage fetching with the current `userDisplayBalanceInfo` endpoint\n- prefer local `amp usage` in Auto mode, with the browser-cookie web path as fallback\n- expose individual and workspace credit balances in the existing Amp card\n- retain the legacy settings-page parser for older deployments\n\nCloses #1317.\nSupersedes #1400 because its fork does not allow maintainer edits. The implementation and contributor credit are preserved from @3kh0.\n\n## Security\n- only the `session` cookie is imported or accepted manually\n- cookies remain limited to HTTPS Amp hosts during redirects\n- diagnostics emit cookie names, never values\n- CLI stdin is closed and execution is bounded by a 15-second timeout\n\n## Proof\n- rebased onto current `main` at `9b22e65b`\n- `swift test --filter Amp` (17 tests)\n- `make check` (0 formatting changes, 0 lint violations)\n- autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings (`gpt-5.5`, confidence 0.82)\n- contributor reports live end-to-end validation with personal and workspace accounts in #1400\n- fresh exact-head CI pending on `a721e5d2826a6840429488907c16ad2259b6f91a`\n\n## Risk\nMedium. This repairs an existing provider but depends on Amp's undocumented authenticated response format. Prepared and fully validated locally; not auto-merged pending authenticated provider product review.\n",
